{% extends 'base.html' %}
{% block body %}
          <div class="hero-unit">
            <h1>pySOS - OGC SOS server</h1><br/>
            <p>pySOS is an attempt at creating a fully fledged PGC SOS server implimentation. pySOS is written in python and is a fully opensource project.</p>
            
          </div>
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span5">
              <h2>OGC</h2>
              <p>The <a href="ogc">Open Geospatial Consortium</a> defines many standards. Have a browse of some of their specs and info sheets</p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span5">
              <h2>Admin Interface</h2>
              <p>This application provides a graphic interface for creating, adding and ammending the services that you offer to the outside world. This allows non python users to manage this service efficiently.</p>
              <p><a class="btn" href="{{ url_for('.admin') }}">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div><!--/span-->
          </div>
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span5">
              <h2>Datasources</h2>
              <p>pySOS allows you to utilise your existing data storage systems instead of duplicating your data for use with the system.  This save space and make people happy. Currently supported datastores are :- PostgreSQL</p>
              <p><a class="btn" href="#">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div><!--/span-->
            <div class="span5">
              <h2>Tests</h2>
              <p>As all good applications should be pySOS is test driven. The tests are accessible through the web interface so you can monitor the happyness of your services.</p>
              <p><a class="btn" href="#">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
          </div><!--/row-->
          
{% endblock %}
